To calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio, we use the formula:

Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets

From the balance sheet at the end of the reporting period (2024-02-01):

- Total Assets = 21,737,442.99  
- Total Liabilities = Total Current Liabilities = 5,637,910.70 (No separate long-term liabilities are listed, so assume all liabilities are current liabilities for this calculation)

Calculate the ratio:

Debt to Asset Ratio = 5,637,910.70 / 21,737,442.99 â‰ˆ 0.2593

Rounded to two decimal places = 0.26
